				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\beta \cos \theta=\frac{k\times \lambda }{D}+4\varepsilon \times \sin \theta$$\end{document}where β is the FWHM, k is a constant, λ is the wavelength of the irradiation, D represents the diameter of the particle, and ε is the lattice strain. Hence, the relation between β×cosθ and 4×sinθ should give a linear line with the slope of strain (ε). The W–H slope was calculated from (002), (110), (202), (220), and (213) planes-sets of the XRD pattern.

